BACKGROUND AND OBJECTIVES: This study estimated years of life lost (YLL) among 
US Latinx individuals during the most recent wave of drug overdose deaths.
METHODS: A serial cross-sectional study of YLL (life expectancy minus age at 
death) from death certificate records of Latinx individuals who died from drug 
overdoses from 2015 to mid-2022.
RESULTS: Over the study period, 58,209 Latinx individuals aged 15-64 years died 
from drug overdoses resulting in 2,266,784 YLL. Age-group YLL differences 
remained stable, but gender YLL trajectories diverged.
CONCLUSIONS AND SCIENTIFIC SIGNIFICANCE: This study extends our understanding of 
the immense loss to Latinx communities from preventable drug deaths.

